The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the President of the United States. These include the nomination of Brendan Carr to be a Member of the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) for the remainder of the term expiring on June 30, 2018, as well as his reappointment for a five-year term starting on July 1, 2018. Additionally, Kay Bailey Hutchison has been nominated to be the United States Permanent Representative on the Council of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) with the rank and status of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary.